“Chaos in the world brings uneasiness, but it also allows the opportunity for creativity and growth.”
Tom Barrett

“Creativity is inventing, experimenting, growing, taking risks, breaking rules, making mistakes, and having fun.”
 Mary Lou Cook (American community activist, calligrapher and author)

“Growth begins when we begin to accept our own weakness”
Jean Vanier

“In the middle of difficulty lies opportunity.”
Albert Einstein

“Before the beginning of great brilliance, there must be chaos. Before a brilliant person begins something great, they must look foolish in the crowd.”
anonymous

“Creativity is the power to connect the seemingly unconnected.”
William Plomer (African born English Writer, 1903-1973)

“Always do what you are afraid to do.”
Ralph Waldo Emerson (American Poet, Lecturer and Essayist, 1803-1882)

“Creativity takes courage.”
Henri Matisse (Artist regarded as the most important French Painter and Artist of the 20th century, 1869-1954)

“A pessimist sees the difficulty in every opportunity; an optimist sees the opportunity in every difficulty.”
Winston Churchill (British Orator, Author and Prime Minister during World War II. 1874-1965)

“Necessity is the mother of invention, it is true, but its father is creativity, and knowledge is the midwife”
Jonathan Schattke

“Creativity often consists of merely turning up what is already there”

“Creativity is the ability to see relationships where none exist.”
Thomas Disch

“Creativity - like human life itself - begins in darkness.”
Julia Cameron